When a spaceship full of scientists landed on Planet Q, they found that $\frac{17}{40}$ of the $160$ aliens had $3$ eyes.  How many aliens had $3$ eyes?
inference: Final Answer: \\boxed{68}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: Remembering that "of" means "times," the number of aliens with 3 eyes is $\frac{17}{40} \cdot 160$.  This equals $\frac{17 \cdot 160}{40}$, which can be rewritten as $17 \cdot \frac{160}{40}$.  Because $160$ divided by $40$ equals $4$, the expression above is the same as $17 \cdot 4$, which equals $\boxed{68}$.
